WEBVTT

00:00:08.895 --> 00:00:15.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus commanded:
‘Let the truth be heard.’

00:00:15.895 --> 00:00:24.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In summer heat, on dusty roads,
He let all hear Jehovah’s word.

00:00:24.645 --> 00:00:32.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He loved God’s sheep
and called to ev’ryone.

00:00:32.104 --> 00:00:41.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He searched the land from the sunrise
‘til the day was done.

00:00:41.062 --> 00:00:48.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From door to door and in the street,
We share with ev’ryone we meet

00:00:48.854 --> 00:00:56.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The news that soon
man’s troubles all will be gone.

00:00:56.645 --> 00:01:05.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Searching the world
For friends of peace in ev’ry nation,

00:01:05.187 --> 00:01:13.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Searching to find
A heart inclined toward salvation,

00:01:13.104 --> 00:01:21.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wanting to leave
No stone unturned.

00:01:22.979 --> 00:01:29.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Time waits for no one,
so the search goes on.

00:01:29.979 --> 00:01:38.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A million hearts, a million lives,
We give our all to save just one.

00:01:38.854 --> 00:01:45.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Love is the force
that makes us call again.

00:01:45.937 --> 00:01:54.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A wounded heart can be healed,
and broken lives can mend.

00:01:54.770 --> 00:02:02.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We search the towns and city squares,
And when we find someone who cares,

00:02:02.895 --> 00:02:10.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The joy we feel
inspires us to go on.

